Sesame oil should be used during a gallbladder diet, hemp helps to strengthen immunity.
A good way to increase the supply of beneficial unsaturated fatty acids from these fruits is to use extra virgin oils.
When cold pressed from seeds, all healthy substances remain in the oil.
Therefore, these oils are also suitable as part of health diets, such as gallbladder oils.
Some extra virgin oils are suitable for the prevention of cardiovascular diseases.
According to the Institute of Health Information and Statistics of the Czech Republic, these have been the most frequent cause of death of Czechs for several years.
Gallbladder inflammations bother mainly women, sesame oil helps.
If you are a lover of Asian cuisine, you must not miss sesame oil in your pantry, which is part of the original recipes for exotic dishes.
Unlike most other oils, it can also be used in cooking food and has a number of beneficial health effects.
It is often used in gallbladder diets.
The essential fatty acids it contains are a good prevention of gallstones.
They are 90% the cause of gallbladder inflammations and women suffer from these problems 3 times more often than men.
In general, gallbladder problems mainly concern overweight people who do not play sports and consume a lot of animal fats.
Sesame oil can also be successfully used in the liver diet, which is very similar to the gallbladder.
If people want to take advantage of all the health benefits of consuming this oil, they should beware of goods from exotic food stores.
Manufacturers from Asia often use over-roasted seeds for pressing, which have a more pronounced taste.
However, the oil will lose all its active substances, said Ladislav Hačecký, executive director of the Czech company Bohemia Olej from Kraslice in the Sokolov region, which produces cold-pressed organic virgin oils.
The company also newly produces sesame oil and uses exclusively unroasted seeds of white sesame.
In an hour, our press can press 8 kilos of sesame.
Mechanical pressing heats the raw material to a maximum of 40 degrees, and therefore the product meets the criteria for the designation of extra virgin.
At higher temperatures, nutrients would be lost.
Sunflower oil is beneficial for diseases of the heart and blood vessels.
The Czech favorite among oils is sunflower.
A survey conducted by Jarmila Hamerská, which she led at Masaryk University, showed that 43% of respondents prefer it in a warm kitchen.
However, it is not really suitable for frying, it starts to burn at 180 ° C.
It is better to use it, for example, to flavor salads and is especially useful in a diet in which it helps prevent cardiovascular diseases.
It contains a high proportion of omega 6 unsaturated fatty acids, which of all fatty acids reduce cholesterol levels the most.
For heart problems, you need to pay attention to the amount of total fat and calories intake.
For example, in one tablespoon of sunflower oil there are 62 calories, in a tablespoon of sea buckthorn oil there are 99 calories.
When it comes to the energy value of food, it is important to realize that natural foods with nutrients are much more suitable than so-called empty calories.
These are part of industrially modified products.
Therefore, it is advisable to reach for extra virgin oils.
The sunflower lasts as long as sesame and hemp for 9 months.
Storing it in the refrigerator extends the shelf life even more.
Old oil people recognize especially by the bitter taste.
On the contrary, the defect is not turbidity at the bottom.
It is a sign that the substance has not been chemically refined.
Hemp oil contains the most healthy acids.
Industrial hemp seeds are among the so-called superfoods, and therefore hemp oil is considered the healthiest of vegetable oils.
This designation owes the highest content of omega 3 and omega 6 unsaturated fatty acids.
These essential fatty acids cannot be produced by the body itself and a person must receive them from food.
Especially important is the intake of omega 3 fatty acids.
A study of scientists published in the European Journal of Clinical Nutrition has shown that the daily intake of this substance is insufficient.
Men in France and Greece consume 0.6 grams, while Icelanders consume 2.5 grams.
The recommended daily dose is 1 to 4 grams.
Hemp oil should be included in the diet as part of a supportive diet to strengthen immunity and heal injuries.
It has anti-inflammatory effects and is an essential part of cell membranes.
People do not have to worry about using hemp oil, it does not contain any psychoactive substances.
The fact that this oil has found its way to consumers is confirmed by the fact that Bohemia Olej's best selling oil is one of the best-selling.
500 litres of it are sold annually.
People often take one tablespoon on an empty stomach in the morning.
Hemp oil is not strong in taste, but it greatly strengthens immunity, advised Daniel Vlček from the Kraslice company Bohemia Olej.
According to statistics, the most passionate nation of barbecue makers are Americans.
There are 1.4 grills per household.
Various barbecue competitions are held all over the world, which only confirm the success of this culinary discipline.
The Czechs are not far behind either.
Based on consumer surveys of the Czech market, we find that only 4% of people have never grilled in their lives.
The vast majority then grill several times a year.
In order for the grilling to be successful, we must not underestimate the preparation - the ideal is to prepare the meat by marinating a few hours before cooking.
Which oil is best for this and at the same time retains healthy substances when grilling?
In general, the grilling process itself should save fat.
Experts agree that a large part of oils begin to lose their taste at high temperatures.
Healthy extra virgin oils then lose the body's beneficial substances, which we otherwise get from them when consuming oils from foods prepared at lower temperatures.
However, this does not mean that extra virgin oils will not find their use when grilling.
Grape oil for grilling, health and beauty.
When you say meat, experts from Bohemia Olej from Kraslice in the Sokolov region immediately think of grape oil.
It wonderfully complements the taste of meat and fish.
In the kitchen is characterized by the unique property of enhancing the natural taste of food.
It is also suitable for frying and grilling, as it has a high degree of combustion, up to 216 ° C.
Even at such a high temperature, it is one of the few oils that retains its health-promoting substances, Daniel Vlček from Bohemia Olej, which is one of the few Czech producers of this oil from the grapevine, describes the benefits of grape oil.
Experts agree that grape oil is 50 times more effective than vitamin E and 20 times more effective than vitamin C.
It also contains high amounts of linoleic acid and is therefore effective in fighting excess cholesterol.
In grape oil, our body also receives important unsaturated fatty acids, vitamins and minerals.
Due to the beneficial content of these substances, it helps reduce high blood pressure, increases metabolism and has a positive effect on the kidneys.
By consuming grape seed oil, we also help to increase our external beauty - it improves skin elasticity, is used in the treatment of acne and helps in the care of dry and brittle hair.
Chefs praise the use of grape oil in the kitchen.
Not only is it suitable for preparing cold dishes, for example when seasoning salads, but also for cooking dishes.
When grilling, it can be used in two ways, marinating and grilling itself.
Marinating meat and fish will preserve their juiciness.
When preparing the marinade, three components must be present: oil, acidity and spices.
For example, add acidity with apple cider vinegar to soften the meat.
Spices add flavor to the meat and preserve the oil and give the right zest, advises Daniel Vlček.
At the same time, he adds that grape oil is ideal for marinating, because it is one of the few oils that can penetrate through dark meat.
So marinated meat or fish are ready for grilling, what to do next?
Extra virgin oils are characterized by the fact that only a few drops are needed to prepare meals.
The same goes for barbecues.
Some oils are completely taboo for this method of preparation.
This applies especially to linseed, hemp and rapeseed oil, which should not be heated at all.
Before grilling, smear the grate with oil to prevent the food from burning.
An essential part of grilling is also the preparation of side dishes.
Grilled meat and fish are suitable for practically anything - grilled vegetables, roasted bread, light vegetable salad and many others.
The chefs from Bohemia Olej recommend, for example, the Hot Summer salad.
For it you need: • 1 piece of peach • 1 bunch of arugula • 1 cup of chopped cucumber • 1 cup of salad leaf mixture • 3 tablespoons of grape oil
